MBOMBELA –   Storm Report South Africa reported that evacuation began in coastal areas. South African paramedics are on their way to assist. They warned the public that people  in the path of this extremely dangerous cyclone Idai should follow available bulletins promptly as most areas are still cut off and communication restricted and will be completely cut off once Idai hits. Beira has no warning systems or sirens in place and it is crucial for word to get out to rural areas and people to assist. ALSO READ: BREAKING NEWS: Evacuation plans for certain areas in Moz due to Cyclone Idai